# Project Rules for AI Assistants

## File Creation Rules
- **Never create .md documentation files** without explicit permission
- **Ask before creating any new files** (except when explicitly requested)
- **Code changes only** - focus on implementation, not documentation
- Keep root directory clean - no unnecessary files

## Communication Style
- Be concise and direct
- Code-first approach
- Explain changes in the response text, not in separate files
- If documentation is needed, ask where to put it first

## Acceptable Files
- Code files (.js, .jsx, .ts, .tsx, etc.)
- Configuration files (.json, .config.js, etc.)
- Component files
- Utility files

## Unacceptable Without Permission
- README files
- Documentation files (.md)
- Guide files
- Summary files
- Action plan files